    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im buying a house in austin and i'm kinda confused. why does the earnest money have to go into an escrow account instead of just going to the seller? also what happens if the inspection comes back and there's like major foundation issues? do i get that money back?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Earnest money goes into escrow because it's a good-faith deposit to show the seller you are serious about buying, and it's held by a neutral third party, like a title company or escrow agent. If you have a major foundation issue after the inspection, you'll have a negotiation. You can ask the seller to make repairs, ask for a credit, or potentially walk away and get your earnest money back, depending on what your contract says. It's important to review your contract details carefully.",
