    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so the escrow agent is basically just sitting on the money while we wait for the inspection stuff to clear? it feels weird that they just hold it there and have all that control over it. what exactly is their job during that waiting period?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow agent is not just sitting on the money; they are the trusted, neutral middleman in the transaction. Their job is to manage the flow of funds, ensure both sides stick to the contract terms, and handle all the paperwork. They are the gatekeepers, making sure the earnest money is only released under the exact conditions outlined in the agreement. Think of them as the chief accountant for the whole deal, making sure everything is properly accounted for.",
      "source": "target",
